HEADWORD: Spermoblast
<hw>Sper"mo*blast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spermo-</ets> + <ets>-blast</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>One of the cells formed by the division of
the spermospore, each of which is destined to become a spermatozoid; a
spermatocyte; a spermatoblast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

